22class StructType : public ZoneObject {
23 public:
24 StructType(uint32_t field_count, uint32_t* field_offsets,
25 const ValueType* reps, const bool* mutabilities)
26 : field_count_(field_count),
27 field_offsets_(field_offsets),
28 reps_(reps),
29 mutabilities_(mutabilities) {}
30
31 uint32_t field_count() const { return field_count_; }
32
33 ValueType field(uint32_t index) const {
34 DCHECK_LT(index, field_count_);
35 return reps_[index];
36 }
37
38 bool mutability(uint32_t index) const {
39 DCHECK_LT(index, field_count_);
40 return mutabilities_[index];
41 }
42
43 // Iteration support.
44 base::iterator_range<const ValueType*> fields() const {
45 return {reps_, reps_ + field_count_};
46 }
47 base::iterator_range<const bool*> mutabilities() const {
48 return {mutabilities_, mutabilities_ + field_count_};
49 }
50
51 bool operator==(const StructType& other) const {
52 if (this == &other) return true;
53 if (field_count() != other.field_count()) return false;
54 return std::equal(fields().begin(), fields().end(),
55 other.fields().begin()) &&
56 std::equal(mutabilities().begin(), mutabilities().end(),
57 other.mutabilities().begin());
58 }
59 bool operator!=(const StructType& other) const { return !(*this == other); }
60
61 // Returns the offset of this field in the runtime representation of the
62 // object, from the start of the object fields (disregarding the object
63 // header).
64 uint32_t field_offset(uint32_t index) const {
65 DCHECK_LT(index, field_count());
66 if (index == 0) return 0;
67 DCHECK(offsets_initialized_);
68 return field_offsets_[index - 1];
69 }
70 uint32_t total_fields_size() const {
71 return field_count() == 0 ? 0 : field_offsets_[field_count() - 1];
72 }
73
74 uint32_t Align(uint32_t offset, uint32_t alignment) {
75 return RoundUp(offset, std::min(alignment, uint32_t{kTaggedSize}));
76 }
77
78 void InitializeOffsets() {
79 if (field_count() == 0) return;
80 DCHECK(!offsets_initialized_);
81 uint32_t offset = field(0).value_kind_size();
82 // Optimization: we track the last gap that was introduced by alignment,
83 // and place any sufficiently-small fields in it.
84 // It's important that the algorithm that assigns offsets to fields is
85 // subtyping-safe, i.e. two lists of fields with a common prefix must
86 // always compute the same offsets for the fields in this common prefix.
87 uint32_t gap_position = 0;
88 uint32_t gap_size = 0;
89 for (uint32_t i = 1; i < field_count(); i++) {
90 uint32_t field_size = field(i).value_kind_size();
91 if (field_size <= gap_size) {
92 uint32_t aligned_gap = Align(gap_position, field_size);
93 uint32_t gap_before = aligned_gap - gap_position;
94 uint32_t aligned_gap_size = gap_size - gap_before;
95 if (field_size <= aligned_gap_size) {
96 field_offsets_[i - 1] = aligned_gap;
97 uint32_t gap_after = aligned_gap_size - field_size;
98 if (gap_before > gap_after) {
99 // Keep old {gap_position}.
100 gap_size = gap_before;
101 } else {
102 gap_position = aligned_gap + field_size;
103 gap_size = gap_after;
104 }
105 continue; // Successfully placed the field in the gap.
106 }
107 }
108 uint32_t old_offset = offset;
109 offset = Align(offset, field_size);
110 uint32_t gap = offset - old_offset;
111 if (gap > gap_size) {
112 gap_size = gap;
113 gap_position = old_offset;
114 }
115 field_offsets_[i - 1] = offset;
116 offset += field_size;
117 }
118 offset = RoundUp(offset, kTaggedSize);
119 field_offsets_[field_count() - 1] = offset;
120#if DEBUG
121 offsets_initialized_ = true;
122#endif
123 }
124
125 // For incrementally building StructTypes.
126 class Builder {
127 public:
128 enum ComputeOffsets : bool {
129 kComputeOffsets = true,
130 kUseProvidedOffsets = false
131 };
132
133 Builder(Zone* zone, uint32_t field_count)
134 : zone_(zone),
135 field_count_(field_count),
136 cursor_(0),
137 field_offsets_(zone_->AllocateArray<uint32_t>(field_count_)),
138 buffer_(
139 zone->AllocateArray<ValueType>(static_cast<int>(field_count))),
140 mutabilities_(
141 zone->AllocateArray<bool>(static_cast<int>(field_count))) {}
142
143 void AddField(ValueType type, bool mutability, uint32_t offset = 0) {
144 DCHECK_LT(cursor_, field_count_);
145 if (cursor_ > 0) {
146 field_offsets_[cursor_ - 1] = offset;
147 } else {
148 DCHECK_EQ(0, offset); // First field always has offset 0.
149 }
150 mutabilities_[cursor_] = mutability;
151 buffer_[cursor_++] = type;
152 }
153
154 void set_total_fields_size(uint32_t size) {
155 if (field_count_ == 0) {
156 DCHECK_EQ(0, size);
157 return;
158 }
159 field_offsets_[field_count_ - 1] = size;
160 }
161
162 StructType* Build(ComputeOffsets compute_offsets = kComputeOffsets) {
163 DCHECK_EQ(cursor_, field_count_);
164 StructType* result = zone_->New<StructType>(field_count_, field_offsets_,
165 buffer_, mutabilities_);
166 if (compute_offsets == kComputeOffsets) {
167 result->InitializeOffsets();
168 } else {
169#if DEBUG
170 bool offsets_specified = true;
171 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < field_count_; i++) {
172 if (field_offsets_[i] == 0) {
173 offsets_specified = false;
174 break;
175 }
176 }
177 result->offsets_initialized_ = offsets_specified;
178#endif
179 }
180 return result;
181 }
182
183 private:
184 Zone* const zone_;
185 const uint32_t field_count_;
186 uint32_t cursor_;
187 uint32_t* field_offsets_;
188 ValueType* const buffer_;
189 bool* const mutabilities_;
190 };
191
192 static const size_t kMaxFieldOffset =
193 (kV8MaxWasmStructFields - 1) * kMaxValueTypeSize;
194
195 private:
196 const uint32_t field_count_;
197#if DEBUG
198 bool offsets_initialized_ = false;
199#endif
200 uint32_t* const field_offsets_;
201 const ValueType* const reps_;
202 const bool* const mutabilities_;
203};
204
205inline std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& out, StructType type) {
206 out << "[";
207 for (ValueType field : type.fields()) {
208 out << field.name() << ", ";
209 }
210 out << "]";
211 return out;
212}
213
214// Support base::hash<StructType>.
215inline size_t hash_value(const StructType& type) {
216 return base::Hasher{}
217 .Add(type.field_count())
218 .AddRange(type.fields())
219 .AddRange(type.mutabilities())
220 .hash();
221}

223class ArrayType : public ZoneObject {
224 public:
225 constexpr explicit ArrayType(ValueType rep, bool mutability)
226 : rep_(rep), mutability_(mutability) {}
227
228 ValueType element_type() const { return rep_; }
229 bool mutability() const { return mutability_; }
230
231 bool operator==(const ArrayType& other) const {
232 return rep_ == other.rep_ && mutability_ == other.mutability_;
233 }
234 bool operator!=(const ArrayType& other) const {
235 return rep_ != other.rep_ || mutability_ != other.mutability_;
236 }
237
238 static const intptr_t kRepOffset;
239
240 private:
241 const ValueType rep_;
242 const bool mutability_;
243};
244
245inline constexpr intptr_t ArrayType::kRepOffset = offsetof(ArrayType, rep_);
246
247// Support base::hash<ArrayType>.
248inline size_t hash_value(const ArrayType& type) {
249 return base::Hasher::Combine(type.element_type(), type.mutability());
250}
